NAME
       GenDo - Amiga Autodoc Generator Command Line Tool

SYNOPSIS
       GenDo [FILES=files] [TO=file] [AMIGAGUIDE] [HTML] [PRESERVEORDER] [VERBOSE] [HELP] [LINELENGTH=n] [WORDWRAP] [CONVERTCOMMENTS] [NOFORMFEED] [NOTOC]

       GenDo #?.c #?.cpp TO mylib.doc [AMIGAGUIDE] [HTML]

DESCRIPTION
       GenDo is a command line tool for Amiga that generates autodoc documentation
       from C/C++ source files containing autodoc comments. The tool can process
       multiple input files and generate both .doc and .guide output formats.

       The tool always generates autodoc documentation (.doc format) and can
       optionally generate additional AmigaGuide (.guide) and HTML output formats.
       The tool supports Amiga wildcard patterns for batch processing of
       multiple files and can generate HTML documentation with individual
       function pages.

PARAMETERS
       FILES=files
              Input source files containing autodoc comments. Multiple files
              can be specified separated by spaces. Supports C and C++ files.
              Can use AmigaDOS wildcard patterns like #?.c

       TO=file
              Output filename for the generated documentation (mandatory).
              The .doc extension is automatically added if not specified.
              For AmigaGuide output, .guide extension is used.
              For HTML output, creates a folder with the base name (i.e. no extension).

       AMIGAGUIDE
              Generate AmigaGuide format output (.guide file) in addition to
              the standard .doc format. Creates a hyperlinked documentation
              with table of contents and navigation.

       HTML   Generate HTML output (folder with index.html) in addition to
              the standard .doc format. Creates individual HTML pages for
              each function with proper navigation and styling.
              The HTML folder uses the base name of the output file (i.e. no extension).

       PRESERVEORDER
              Preserve the original order of functions in the output instead
              of sorting them alphabetically. By default, functions are
              sorted alphabetically by name.

       VERBOSE
              Enable verbose output showing processing details, file parsing
              status, and debug information.

       LINELENGTH=n
              Set maximum line length for output (default: 78 characters).
              Controls text wrapping and formatting.

       WORDWRAP
              Enable word wrapping for long lines (default: enabled).
              Automatically wraps text to fit within specified line length.

       CONVERTCOMMENTS
              Convert backslashes to forward slashes in comments.
              Useful for cross-platform compatibility.

       NOFORMFEED
              Disable form feed characters in output.
              Prevents page breaks between sections.

       NOTOC
              Disable table of contents generation.
              Reduces output size for simple documentation.


AUTODOC FORMAT
       GenDo parses autodoc comments in the following format:

       /**
        * NAME
        *       function_name - Brief description
        *
        * SYNOPSIS
        *       return_type function_name(parameters);
        *
        * FUNCTION
        *       Detailed description of what the function does.
        *
        * INPUTS
        *       param1 - Description of first parameter
        *       param2 - Description of second parameter
        *
        * RESULT
        *       Description of return value
        *
        * NOTES
        *       Additional notes and implementation details
        *
        * SEE ALSO
        *       related_function(3), other_function(3)
        */

       Supported sections:
       - NAME: Function name and brief description
       - SYNOPSIS: Function signature
       - FUNCTION: Detailed description
       - INPUTS: Parameter descriptions
       - RESULT: Return value description
       - NOTES: Additional information
       - SEE ALSO: Related functions
       - BUGS: Known issues
       - EXAMPLE: Usage examples

EXAMPLES
       Generate documentation from single file:
              GenDo FILES=myfile.c TO mylib.doc

       Generate documentation with AmigaGuide output:
              GenDo FILES=myfile.c TO mylib.doc AMIGAGUIDE

       Generate documentation with HTML output:
              GenDo FILES=myfile.c TO mylib.doc HTML

       Generate documentation with both AmigaGuide and HTML:
              GenDo FILES=myfile.c TO mylib.doc AMIGAGUIDE HTML

       Process multiple files with wildcards:
              GenDo FILES=#?.c,#?.cpp TO mylib.doc

       Process with verbose output and preserve order:
              GenDo FILES=#?.c TO mylib.doc PRESERVEORDER VERBOSE

       Generate only AmigaGuide format:
              GenDo FILES=*.c TO mylib.guide AMIGAGUIDE

       Generate HTML documentation folder:
              GenDo FILES=*.c TO mylib.doc HTML

       Generate with custom line length and word wrap:
              GenDo FILES=myfile.c TO mylib.doc LINELENGTH=100 WORDWRAP

       Generate with form feed disabled:
              GenDo FILES=myfile.c TO mylib.doc NOFORMFEED

       Generate with table of contents disabled:
              GenDo FILES=myfile.c TO mylib.doc NOTOC

RETURN CODES
       0 (RETURN_OK)     Success
       5 (RETURN_WARN)   Warning (e.g., no autodocs found)
       10 (RETURN_ERROR) Error (invalid arguments, file not found)
       20 (RETURN_FAIL)  Severe error

FEATURES
       - Parse autodoc comments from C/C++ source files and generate Autodocs
       - Support for multiple input files with wildcard patterns
       - Generate .doc, .guide, and HTML output formats
       - AmigaGuide hyperlinked documentation with navigation
       - HTML documentation with individual function pages
       - Smart target file naming with automatic extensions
       - Alphabetical sorting of functions (can be disabled)
       - Character encoding conversion (UTF-8 to Latin-1)
       - Verbose output option
       - Table of contents generation


LIMITATIONS
       - Maximum input files: Limited by available memory
       - Maximum autodoc entries: 1000

REQUIREMENTS
       - Amiga operating system 3.0 or higher
       - SAS/C compiler for building


BUILDING
       To build GenDo on AmigaOS:
              smake

       To install to SDK:C/ directory:
              smake install

       To clean build artifacts:
              smake clean

       To run tests:
              execute test_gendo

NOTES
       - Input files are processed in the order they appear on command line
       - Function names are extracted from the NAME section of autodocs
       - Output files are created in the current directory unless path specified
       - Character encoding is converted from UTF-8 to Latin-1 for Amiga compatibility
       - HTML folders are created with the base name of the output file, without any extension
       - Smart filename handling automatically adds .doc extension if missing

